HEADWORD: Gestatory
<hw>Ges"ta*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>gestatorius</ets> that serves for carrying: cf. F.
<ets>gestatoire</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to gestation or pregnancy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Capable of being carried or worn.</def> <mark>[Obs.
or R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
